Sentencas: In this work, the commercial SUS430 ferritic stainless steel was used as the current collector to study the fracture behaviors of the planar electrolyte-supported and anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with the size of 10 cm x 10 cm during the thermal cycle process.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode-supported cells (ASCs) were fabricated by tape-casting, spraying, screen-printing and co-sintering.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrolyte-supported cells (ESCs) using fully-stabilized zirconia as material were prepared by tape-casting, multilayer lamination, screen-printing and co-sintering.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The output power densities at 0.7 V (P(0.7V) )of the anode-supported and electrolyte-supported cells could reach 0.60 W cm(-2) and 0.43 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: During the thermal cycle testing, the ESC sample was cracked, while the ASC sample had no obvious changes.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of the different samples was studied, and the two cells were characterized by the XRD after the thermal cycle testing.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the fracture behaviors of the two cells were discussed.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicated that the ASC sample had the good stability during the thermal cycle testing.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent anti-cracking performance of the ASC was attributable to two aspects.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Firstly, the TEC of the anode support is more close to that of the SUS430 material; secondly, the phase transformation of zirconia from monoclinic phase to tetragonal phase induced by stress is favorable for contraction of the anode support layer during the cooling process.
Titulo: Study on the fracture behavior of the planar-type solid oxide fuel cells
